https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/5GnU2y716LdiS28WUz9q5uWq9ak.jpg Demolition expert Ned lives in a nice new house on the edge of the English countryside. He loves his job. Barbeques. Car boot sales. His life is entirely unremarkable. So why has he not slept a wink in six months? Why is he so terrified of his wife? Parlour Song is a satirical exploration of deceit, paranoia and desire in leafy surburbia. Digital Theatre: Parlour Song
